The paper discusses the application of intelligent search strategies to solve Constraint Satisfaction Problems (CSP) using Constraint Handling Rules (CHR). This involves the use of adaptive constraint processing and the comparison of different search strategies. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the implementation of CHR in Java and SICStus Prolog, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the comparison of different search strategies involves the analysis of their runtime and efficiency, which could place the paper in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the paper involves the comparison of different implementations, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
